This paper is about Named Entity Recognition (NER) which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as Canonical Correlation Analysis (CCA) and co-training, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of embeddings, which is a popular technique in Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper focuses on the task of NER, which is a subfield of Named Entity Recognition and Classification (cs.NE).
